{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775843738197,"sessionID":"ses_2877ac962ffeKMaCzX7oWK7UCv","part":{"id":"prt_d788901c5001HfClDvf9RAWqcj","messageID":"msg_d78865cb5001dihuu9m29mZN7D","sessionID":"ses_2877ac962ffeKMaCzX7oWK7UCv","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-74ae4456bb014505b39a8dbd56372ab3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md","content":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation - Common Types & Constants\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` file\n  - Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct with fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace`\n  - Define `CreateSandboxResponse` struct with fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `SandboxName`, `EntryPoints`\n  - Define `SandboxEntryPoint` struct with fields: `Path`, `Protocol`, `Endpoint`\n  - Define `SandboxInfo` struct with fields: `Kind`, `SandboxID`, `SandboxNamespace`, `Name`, `SessionID`, `CreatedAt`, `ExpiresAt`, `Status`, `EntryPoints`, `UserToken`, `ServiceAccount`, `ServiceAccountName`\n  - Add JSON tags using camelCase for all fields\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/common/types/...`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create `pkg/common/types/sandbox_test.go` file\n  - Test `CreateSandboxRequest.Validate()` method:\n    - Kind must be \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    - Namespace must be non-empty\n    - Name must be non-empty\n    - Return appropriate error messages\n  - Test JSON serialization/deserialization for all types\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/common/types/... -v`\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` file\n  - Define constants:\n    - `DefaultSandboxTTL = 8 * time.Hour`\n    - `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n    - `DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour`\n    - `DefaultSessionTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n    - `SandboxCreationTimeout = 2 * time.Minute`\n    - `SandboxDeleteTimeout = 30 * time.Second`\n  - Define label/annotation key constants:\n    - `LabelKeySessionID = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"`\n    - `LabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"`\n    - `LabelKeySandboxName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"`\n    - `LabelKeyManagedBy = \"managed-by\"`\n    - `AnnotationKeyIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"`\n    - `AnnotationKeyPodName = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"`\n  - Define GVR constants:\n    - `SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}`\n    - `SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}`\n  - Define kind constants:\n    - `SandboxKind = \"Sandbox\"`\n    - `SandboxClaimKind = \"SandboxClaim\"`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T1.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults_test.go` file\n  - Test all constant values match design specification\n  - Test GVR constants are correctly formed\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestDefaults -v`\n\n### Phase 2: K8s Client Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` file\n  - Define `K8sClient` struct with fields:\n    - `dynamicClient dynamic.Interface`\n    - `informerFactory externalversions.SharedInformerFactory`\n    - `agentRuntimeLister listers.AgentRuntimeLister`\n    - `codeInterpreterLister listers.CodeInterpreterLister`\n    - `podLister corev1listers.PodLister`\n    - `coreClient kubernetes.Interface`\n  - Define `ClientCache` struct for per-user client caching (if auth enabled)\n  - Implement `NewK8sClient(config *rest.Config) (*K8sClient, error)` function\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go` file\n  - Test `K8sClient` initialization with fake clientset\n  - Test informer factory creation\n  - Test lister access methods\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestK8sClient -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` file\n  - Define `Informers` struct wrapping `SharedInformerFactory`\n  - Implement `NewInformers(k8sClient *K8sClient) *Informers` function\n  - Implement `Start(ctx context.Context)` method\n  - Implement `WaitForCacheSync(ctx context.Context) bool` method\n  - Implement `GetAgentRuntimeInformer() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer` method\n  - Implement `GetCodeInterpreterInformer() runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer` method\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go` file\n  - Test informer start and stop\n  - Test cache sync with timeout\n  - Test lister retrieval\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestInformers -v`\n\n### Phase 3: Store Integration\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Define Store interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n  - Add `Store` interface with methods:\n    - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n    - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n    - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n    - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n    - `ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Create Store implementation stub (interface only for now)\n  - Note: Actual Redis Store implementation is in AR-006 or separate module\n  - Create mock Store for testing purposes\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n### Phase 4: Sandbox Controller & Watcher\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` file\n  - Define `SandboxReconciler` struct with fields:\n    - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n    - `watchers map[string]chan struct{}`\n    - `mutex sync.RWMutex`\n  - Implement `WatchSandboxOnce(namespace, name string) (<-chan struct{}, error)` method:\n    - Register watcher before CR creation\n    - Return channel that closes when sandbox enters \"running\" state\n  - Implement `notifyWatcher(namespace, name string)` private method\n  - Implement `getSandboxStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (string, error)` method\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller_test.go` file\n  - Test `WatchSandboxOnce` registration\n  - Test watcher channel closes on running status\n  - Test concurrent watchers\n  - Test watcher cleanup\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestSandboxController -v`\n\n### Phase 5: Workload Builder\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` file\n  - Implement `buildSandboxObject(runtime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n    - Generate sandbox name: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n    - Set APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n    - Set Kind: `Sandbox`\n    - Set labels: session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by\n    - Set annotations: idle-timeout\n    - Set spec.podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n    - Set spec.replicas = 1\n    - Set spec.lifecycle.shutdownTime = now + MaxSessionDuration\n  - Implement `RandString(n int) string` helper for 8-char lowercase random string\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` file\n  - Test `buildSandboxObject` with valid AgentRuntime:\n    - Verify name format (workload-8char)\n    - Verify labels and annotations\n    - Verify podTemplate copied correctly\n    - Verify replicas = 1\n  - Test `RandString` generates 8 lowercase letters\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildSandboxObject -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject(ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n  - Set APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n  - Set Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n  - Minimal metadata (labels and annotations)\n  - No full PodSpec\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Create test for `buildSandboxClaimObject`:\n  - Verify correct GVK\n  - Verify minimal metadata\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildSandboxClaimObject -v`\n\n- [ ] **T5.5** Implement `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxObject(ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string, publicKey []byte) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error)`:\n  - Build full Sandbox for WarmPoolSize == 0\n  - Single container named \"code-interpreter\"\n  - Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var if AuthMode=picod and publicKey available\n  - Set default ports if spec.Ports empty: `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: HTTP, PathPrefix: \"/\"}]`\n  - Apply optional fields: Command, Args, Environment, Resources, RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T5.6** Create test for `buildCodeInterpreterSandboxObject`:\n  - Test with AuthMode=picod: verify public key injected\n  - Test with AuthMode=none: verify no public key\n  - Test with empty Ports: verify default 8080\n  - Test with custom Ports: verify copied correctly\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildCodeInterpreterSandbox -v`\n\n### Phase 6: Sandbox Creator - Core Creation Flow\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` file\n  - Define `sandboxCreator` struct with fields:\n    - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n    - `sandboxController *SandboxReconciler`\n    - `storeClient Store`\n    - `publicKey []byte`\n  - Implement `newSandboxCreator(...)` constructor\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Implement `createSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured, isWarmPool bool, userClient dynamic.Interface) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`:\n  - Phase 1: Register watcher (WatchSandboxOnce)\n  - Phase 2: Store placeholder SandboxInfo (status=pending)\n  - Phase 3: Create CR via dynamic client\n  - Phase 4: Wait for running (2-minute timeout)\n  - Phase 5: Resolve Pod IP and entryPoints\n  - Phase 6: Update Store with full SandboxInfo (status=running)\n  - Implement rollback on each phase failure\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` file\n  - Test successful creation flow:\n    - Mock watcher channel (close immediately)\n    - Mock dynamic client Create\n    - Mock Store operations\n    - Verify correct SandboxInfo returned\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestCreateSandbox_Success -v`\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Test creation timeout:\n  - Mock watcher channel that never closes\n  - Use 2-minute timeout context\n  - Verify CR deleted after timeout\n  - Verify Store record deleted\n  - Verify error returned\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestCreateSandbox_Timeout -v`\n\n- [ ] **T6.5** Test rollback on creation failure:\n  - Mock dynamic client Create failure\n  - Verify Store placeholder deleted\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestCreateSandbox_Rollback -v`\n\n- [ ] **T6.6** Test rollback on IP resolution failure:\n  - Mock successful CR creation\n  - Mock resolvePodIP failure\n  - Verify CR deleted\n  - Verify Store record deleted\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestCreateSandbox_IPResolutionFailure -v`\n\n### Phase 7: Pod IP Resolution & EntryPoint Building\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Implement `resolvePodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName string) (string, error)` in `sandbox_creator.go`:\n  - Priority 1: Use sandbox name as pod name\n  - Priority 2: Check sandbox annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`\n  - Priority 3: Get pod from podLister, verify Phase=Running and PodIP non-empty\n  - Priority 4: Fallback: list pods by label `SandboxNameLabelKey`, match owner reference\n  - Return error if no running pod found\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Create tests for `resolvePodIP`:\n  - Test with pod name matching sandbox name\n  - Test with annotation override\n  - Test with pod not running (Phase != Running)\n  - Test with owner reference matching\n  - Test with no pod found\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestResolvePodIP -v`\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Implement `resolveEntryPoints(ctx context.Context, namespace, sandboxName string, ports []runtimev1alpha1.TargetPort) ([]types.SandboxEntryPoint, error)`:\n  - Call resolvePodIP to get pod IP\n  - Call buildEntryPoints with pod IP and ports\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T7.4** Implement `buildEntryPoints(podIP string, ports []runtimev1alpha1.TargetPort) []types.SandboxEntryPoint`:\n  - Iterate over ports\n  - Build SandboxEntryPoint: `{Path: p.PathPrefix, Protocol: string(p.Protocol), Endpoint: fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", podIP, p.Port)}`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T7.5** Create tests for `buildEntryPoints`:\n  - Test with multiple ports\n  - Test with HTTP and HTTPS protocols\n  - Test endpoint format: `ip:port`\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -run TestBuildEntryPoints -v`\n\n### Phase 8: HTTP Handlers\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_handler.go` file\n  - Define `SandboxHandler` struct with fields:\n    - `creator *sandboxCreator`\n    - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n    - `logger Logger`\n  - Implement `Register(r chi.Router)` method:\n    - POST /v1/agent-runtime\n    - POST /v1/code-interpreter\n    - DELETE /v1/sessions/:sessionId (optional, for cleanup)\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n\n- [ ] **T8.2** Implement `handleAgentRuntimeCreate(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)`:\n  - Parse JSON request body into `CreateSandboxRequest`\n  - Override Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"\n  - Validate request (call Validate() method)\n  - Get AgentRuntime from informer lister\n  - Check if runtime.Spec.Template != nil (return 400 if nil)\n  - Generate sessionID (UUID)\n  - Call buildSandboxObject\n  - Call createSandbox\n  - Build CreateSandboxResponse\n  - Return 200 with JSON response\n  - Handle errors: 400 (validation), 404 (not found), 500 (internal)\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n\n- [ ] **T8.3** Implement `handleCodeInterpreterCreate(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)`:\n  - Parse JSON request body\n  - Override Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n  - Validate request\n  - Get CodeInterpreter from informer lister\n  - Check WarmPoolSize:\n    - If > 0: buildSandboxClaimObject, createSandbox with isWarmPool=true\n    - If == 0: buildCodeInterpreterSandboxObject, createSandbox\n  - Inject public key if AuthMode=picod\n  - Apply default ports if Ports empty\n  - Return CreateSandboxResponse\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n\n- [ ] **T8.4** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_handler_test.go` file\n  - Test WM-001: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Success`:\n    - Mock AgentRuntime in fake informer\n    - Mock createSandbox success\n    - Verify 200 response with sessionId and entryPoints\n  - Test WM-002: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Idempotent`:\n    - Mock Store with existing sessionID\n    - Verify same sessionId returned\n  - Test WM-003: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_MissingPodTemplate`:\n    - Mock AgentRuntime with Template=nil\n    - Verify 400 response with \"pod template\" message\n  - Test invalid request body (JSON parse error)\n  - Test validation errors (empty name/namespace)\n  - Test not found error (Informer returns IsNotFound)\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate -v`\n\n- [ ] **T8.5** Create tests for CodeInterpreter handler:\n  - Test WarmPool path (WarmPoolSize > 0)\n  - Test default ports (Ports empty)\n  - Test AuthMode=picod with public key injection\n  - Test AuthMode=none without public key\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate -v`\n\n### Phase 9: Error Handling & Response Formatting\n\n- [ ] **T9.1** Implement error mapping in handlers:\n  - JSON bind error → 400: `{\"message\":\"Invalid request body\"}`\n  - Validation error → 400: `{\"message\":\"<field> is required\"}`\n  - Template missing → 400: `{\"message\":\"agent runtime not found: ... pod template missing\"}`\n  - Not found → 404: `{\"message\":\"agent runtime not found\"}`\n  - Timeout → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n  - K8s API error → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n  - Store error → 500: `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n\n- [ ] **T9.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/response.go` file:\n  - Implement `writeJSONResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, data interface{})` helper\n  - Implement `writeErrorResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, message string)` helper\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/...`\n\n- [ ] **T9.3** Create tests for error response formatting:\n  - Test each error type produces correct status and JSON\n  - Verify Content-Type: application/json header\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/... -run TestErrorResponse -v`\n\n### Phase 10: Authentication Middleware\n\n- [ ] **T10.1** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/auth.go` file\n  - Define context keys:\n    - `contextKeyUserToken`\n    - `contextKeyServiceAccount`\n    - `contextKeyServiceAccountName`\n    - `contextKeyNamespace`\n  - Implement `authMiddleware(publicKey []byte, enableAuth bool) func(http.Handler) http.Handler`:\n    - If EnableAuth=false: pass through\n    - If EnableAuth=true:\n      - Extract Bearer token from Authorization header\n      - Validate token via Kubernetes TokenReview API\n      - Extract ServiceAccount name and namespace\n      - Store token and SA info in context\n      - Return 401 if missing/invalid token\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/...`\n\n- [ ] **T10.2** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/auth_test.go` file\n  - Test with EnableAuth=false: no validation\n  - Test with valid Bearer token: context populated\n  - Test with missing Authorization header: 401\n  - Test with invalid token: 401\n  - Test TokenReview API call\n  - Verify: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/... -run TestAuthMiddleware -v`\n\n- [ ] **T10.3** Implement per-user client creation (if auth enabled):\n  - Modify `sandboxCreator` to accept userClient from context\n  - Implement `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient(token string, namespace string) (dynamic.Interface, error)` in k8s_client.go\n  - Cache clients by token+namespace\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n### Phase 11: Server Integration\n\n- [ ] **T11.1** Update `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`:\n  - Add fields to `HTTPServer` struct:\n    - `k8sClient *K8sClient`\n    - `informers *Informers`\n    - `sandboxController *SandboxReconciler`\n    - `storeClient Store`\n    - `publicKey []byte`\n    - `enableAuth bool`\n  - Implement `NewHTTPServerWithWorkloadManager(cfg Config, k8sClient *K8sClient, storeClient Store, publicKey []byte, enableAuth bool, logger Logger) (*HTTPServer, error)`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n- [ ] **T11.2** Implement server initialization sequence:\n  - Initialize Informers\n  - Start informers and wait for cache sync (timeout 1 minute)\n  - Initialize SandboxReconciler\n  - Initialize sandboxCreator\n  - Initialize SandboxHandler\n  - Register middleware: Recovery → Logging → CORS → Auth → SandboxHandler\n